You'll need to install some additional pieces inorder for this to work:

------------------------

For use with Linux and LibreOffice:

1. You'll need a macro that opens LibreOffice and prints the file
http://www.togaware.com/linux/survivor/Convert_MS_Word.html

[2]. You may also elect to find addition Microsoft fonts:
http://www.oooninja.com/2008/01/calibri-linux-vista-fonts-download.html

------------------------

For use with OS X:

We'll piggyback on QuickLook, then use this library to PDF the file
http://code.google.com/p/wkhtmltopdf/

------------------------
------------------------

This script is a polling script so you'll need to keep it running in the background in order for it to work.

After configuring for your installation at the top of the file, run:

$ python pdfdropoff.py &


